### Aspect Oriented Programming

- Use this programming model when you want to inject execution of certain logic before or after a service method is executed.
- By looking at the service code no developer can understand whether additional logic around execution of service method because no such annotation or markings are used in service class.
- It is only understood by looking at the expression used with @Before and @After annotations.

Joinpoint
- Program execution flow. Methods that are called during the flow of execution

Advice
- the set of instructions that are executed. actual action to be taken either before or after the method execution.
- This is the actual piece of code that's executed.

PointCut
- the point in a joinpoint where the advice is executed.